<p>Google Image Search, where you can search by very broad license type (note: don’t just assume that because something shows up here, it is CC-BY-SA compatible; check!)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Just wanna explain how to do this: search a thing in Google, click the Images tab, click Tools, click Usage Rights, and then click the one you want. &quot;Labeled for reuse&quot; is the safest umbrella one, I have found, because you don't know if someone will make a t-shirt based on the article you put it on and then all of a sudden 'noncommercial' won't apply anymore and you also don't want to have to deal with determining whether or not you edited the image enough to qualify as &quot;modification.&quot; It's also a good idea to check the source site for licensing information just on the off-chance Google is wrong, even though it's unlikely.</p>

