			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2742966">
									

<p>Actually this is really important!</p>
<p>Photos taken by the US government and released to the public are normally public domain. So NASA, NPS, USDA, etc. photos are all fair to use. This also applies to many other countries as well. For example, the photos I used in <a href="/the-journal-of-k-m-sandoval">The Journal of K. M. Sandoval</a> were all taken by the Italian government and are also public domain. I recommend double checking to be sure, but it's usually very straightforward and easy to find.</p>

