<p>The wiki uses US copyright law, so all images published before 1923 are in the public domain and therefore can be freely used in articles. Next year, works published in 1923 enter the public domain, and 1924 in 2020, etc. so we'll have more images to use!</p>
<p>I use <a href="https://www.gutenberg.org">Project Gutenberg</a> for reading, but it also has some great collections of images (the vast majority of which are public domain in the USA). A few you might use for fuel (please don't hotlink; PG doesn't like it!)&#8230;</p>
<p>Categories:</p>
<p><a href="https://www.gutenberg.org/wiki/Art_(Bookshelf)">Art</a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/subject/3605">Picture Books for Children</a></p>
